<div id="icons" class="container">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Icons</h1>
  </div>
  <p>
    We use a custom icon font from <a href="http://icomoon.io/app" target="_blank">Icomoon</a>. We will add and customize as necessary.
    Here are the icons we currently support:
  </p>
  <p>
    <div class="icon-multiple"> multiple</div>
    <div class="icon-ascending"> ascending</div>
    <div class="icon-descending"> descending</div>
    <div class="icon-left"> left</div>
    <div class="icon-right"> right</div>
    <div class="icon-play"> play</div>
    <div class="icon-alert"> alert</div>
    <div class="icon-favorite"> favorite</div>
    <div class="icon-share"> share</div>
    <div class="icon-code"> code</div>
    <div class="icon-lock"> lock</div>
    <div class="icon-buy"> buy</div>
    <div class="icon-print"> print</div>
    <div class="icon-rotate-right"> rotate right</div>
    <div class="icon-rotate-left"> rotate left</div>
    <div class="icon-delete"> delete</div>
    <div class="icon-zoom-out"> zoom out</div>
    <div class="icon-zoom-in"> zoom in</div>
    <div class="icon-book"> book</div>
    <div class="icon-triangle-right"> triangle right</div>
    <div class="icon-triangle-down"> triangle down</div>
    <div class="icon-tag"> tag</div>
    <div class="icon-video"> video</div>
    <div class="icon-video-play"> video play</div>
    <div class="icon-video-pause"> video pause</div>
    <div class="icon-mute"> mute</div>
    <div class="icon-volume"> volume</div>
    <div class="icon-save"> save</div>
    <div class="icon-first"> first</div>
    <div class="icon-edit"> edit</div>
    <div class="icon-trash"> trash</div>
    <div class="icon-cog"> cog</div>
    <div class="icon-user"> user</div>
    <div class="icon-eye"> eye</div>
    <div class="icon-search"> search</div>
  </p>
  <p>
    There are a few ways you can add icons. First, as a class:
  </p>
  <p class="code">
    <code class="prettyprint">
      &lt;div class="icon-zoom-out"&gt; zoom out&lt;/div&gt;<br />
      &lt;div class="icon-zoom-in"&gt; zoom in&lt;/div&gt;
    </code>
  </p>
  <p>
    Second, as a data-icon attribute
  </p>
  <p class="code">
    <code class="prettyprint">
      &lt;div data-icon="-"&gt; zoom out&lt;/div&gt;<br />
      &lt;div data-icon="+"&gt; zoom in&lt;/div&gt;
    </code>
  </p>
  <p>
    Third, directly in the CSS
  </p>
  <p class="code">
    <code class="prettyprint">
      .icon-zoom-out:before { content: "-"; }<br />
      .icon-zoom-in:before { content: "+"; }
    </code>
  </p>
</div>


